  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper, we obtain the light neutrino masses and mixings consistent with the experiments, in the democratic texture approach. The essential ansatz is that <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>ν</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></math> are assumed to transform as “right-handed fields” <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mn mathvariant="bold">2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">R</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mn mathvariant="bold">1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="bold">R</mi></mrow></msub></math> under the <math altimg="si11.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub><mo>×</mo><msub><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></msub></math> symmetry. The symmetry breaking terms are assumed to be diagonal and hierarchical. This setup only allows the normal hierarchy of the neutrino mass, and excludes both of inverted hierarchical and degenerated neutrinos.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
